---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import RedactedText from "../components/RedactedText.astro";
---

<Layout title="About | The Civic Chronic">
    <Header />

    <main
        class="flex-grow flex flex-col items-center pt-32 pb-20 px-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto min-h-screen"
    >
        <h1
            class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-ink mb-12 text-center"
        >
            About The Archive
        </h1>

        <div
            class="prose prose-lg text-gray-800 leading-relaxed space-y-8 font-light"
        >
            <p
                class="text-xl leading-relaxed border-l-4 border-primary pl-6 italic"
            >
                "The Civic Chronic is a digital monument to the <RedactedText
                    text="efficiency"
                    hint="INCOMPETENCE"
                /> of modern systems."
            </p>

            <h3
                class="font-bold text-xl text-ink font-serif mt-12 mb-4 uppercase tracking-widest"
            >
                Mission Statement
            </h3>
            <p>
                We live in an era of unprecedented data, yet the most important
                stories—the quiet failures of infrastructure and policy—are
                often buried under mountains of paperwork. This archive exists
                to <strong class="font-bold text-primary">excavate</strong> those
                stories.
            </p>
            <p>
                We do not protest. We do not lobby. We simply observe. By
                collecting the receipts, permits, and timestamps of dysfunction,
                we ensure that nothing is truly lost to the shredder.
            </p>

            <h3
                class="font-bold text-xl text-ink font-serif mt-12 mb-4 uppercase tracking-widest"
            >
                Our Methodology
            </h3>
            <p>
                Every case file in our archive undergoes a rigorous verification
                process. We look for specific criteria that define a "Systemic
                Failure":
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 marker:text-primary">
                <li>
                    <strong>Scale:</strong> Does the failure impact a significant
                    population or waste >$1M in resources?
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Absurdity:</strong> Is the outcome diametrically opposed
                    to the stated intent? (e.g., a "Paperless Initiative" that increases
                    paper usage).
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Silence:</strong> Has the issue been ignored or buried
                    by official channels?
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h3
                class="font-bold text-xl text-ink font-serif mt-12 mb-4 uppercase tracking-widest"
            >
                About This Project
            </h3>
            <p>
                <em>The Civic Chronic</em> is a portfolio piece designed to explore
                <strong>Brutalist Web Design</strong> and <strong
                    >Interactive Storytelling</strong
                >. It is built with <a
                    href="https://astro.build"
                    target="_blank"
                    class="underline decoration-primary hover:text-primary transition-colors"
                    >Astro 5</a
                > and <a
                    href="https://tailwindcss.com"
                    target="_blank"
                    class="underline decoration-primary hover:text-primary transition-colors"
                    >Tailwind CSS v4</a
                >.
            </p>
            <p>
                While the specific cases presented here are satirical fiction,
                they are inspired by real-world events. Any resemblance to
                actual bureaucratic disasters is purely coincidental.
            </p>

            <div
                class="mt-12 p-6 bg-gray-100 border-t border-b border-gray-200 text-center"
            >
                <p class="text-sm font-medium italic text-gray-600">
                    "The bureaucracy is expanding to meet the needs of the
                    expanding bureaucracy." — Oscar Wilde
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>

    <Footer />
</Layout>
